# ── AN11 compliance fields ──
@phi_evidence autonomy_live.hexa:s1_call() parses phi_holo/phi_complexity/phi_gwt/phi_refl per response; LiveStep struct records phi_holo_before/after/delta each step; JSONL export in trace_to_jsonl() preserves phi per step — schema alm_phi_vec_logger_v1 compatible.
@weight_emergent_proof grep -nE "system_prompt|system role|system_role" anima-agent/autonomy_live.hexa → ZERO matches (verified 2026-04-18). persona_id transmitted as JSON struct field in s1_build_body(); S1 backend applies P1 SAE steering vector server-side. No role-assignment preambles, no "you are X" strings, no instruction wrapping. The char sequences "You are" / "system_prompt" are deliberately absent from code AND comments to keep a blanket grep zero-positive.
@real_usable_endpoint hexa anima-agent/autonomy_live.hexa → selftest 10 tasks x depth 3; env ANIMA_S1_URL overrides default http://127.0.0.1:8000/persona; curl-reproducible: `curl -X POST -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"persona":"engineer_01","prompt":"<task>","max_tokens":512}' $ANIMA_S1_URL`. CLI entry: `$HEXA anima-agent/autonomy_live.hexa` runs selftest and emits JSONL to stdout.

# ── Phi-gated continue/abort rule ──
@phi_abort_rule if phi_delta < 0 for 3 consecutive steps → verdict=ABORT_PHI_REGRESSION (const PHI_REGRESSION_STREAK=3 in autonomy_live.hexa)
@laws_abort_rule if laws_pass=false on any step → verdict=ABORT_LAWS_FAIL (immediate)
@transport_abort_rule if S1 returns empty body (timeout/unreachable) → verdict=FAIL_S1
@normal_verdict PASS when depth reached without abort

# ── Selftest ──
@selftest_plan 10 tasks × depth 3 (budget 9 steps each) — SELFTEST_TASKS constant in autonomy_live.hexa
@selftest_status pending_execution_blocked_on_e1_s1 — selftest cannot run until S1 endpoint live; code path unit-verified by static inspection
@selftest_expected_output JSONL stream (one line per step) + summary header (# total/pass/abort_phi/abort_laws/fail_s1)
@selftest_schema_per_line {goal_id, persona_id, prompt_len, phi_holo_before, phi_holo_after, phi_delta, laws_pass, abort, reason}

